other_tests.findings: Several large fragments of tumor were sent to pathology; post-treatment bronchoscopy showed that the right main stem bronchus was patent.
Biopsy of the costosternal mass revealed metastatic adenocarcinoma of the lung.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Complete resolution of the costosternal metastasis after chemoradiation therapy.

other_tests.findings: Tumor involving the carina with extension into the proximal medial wall of the left main stem bronchus with 80% occlusion.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Post-treatment, the occlusion was cleared; patient is alive 9 years after presentation.

other_tests.findings: Showed a solid heterogeneously enhancing multilobulated mass in the superior segment of the right upper lobe; metastasis to subcarinal lymph node and probable metastatic disease to conglomerated right perihilar lymph nodes.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Pretreatment AFP level was 4410 ng/ml; post-treatment AFP level was 1 ng/ml.
